Example<script>
  document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = "My First JavaScript";
</script>

Most JavaScript programs contain many JavaScript statements. Semicolons separate JavaScript statements. The statements are executed, one by one, in the same order as they are written. In this example, x, y, and are given values, and finally z is displayed: 

//Example: a and b are variables
var x = 2;
var y = 7;
var z = x + y;
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = z;

